                <head>No. 276.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Evarts</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">White</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1880-05-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 19, 1880</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 102.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                    dispatch No. 115, of the 26th ultimo, and to inform you in reply that this
                    Department is pleased to learn from your report of the opening of the
                    International Fishery Exhibition that the display made by the American
                    department was so creditable to this country. In this connection I desire to
                    commend the happy spirit of your speech on the occasion of the opening of the
                    exhibition as well calculated to strengthen the friendly relations already
                    existing between the two countries.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WM. M. EVARTS.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
